"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855591","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>This data is not held centrally and can only be collated at disproportionate cost. Where staff are working in approved premises if they hold no vetting they will be supervised at all times by permanent, vetted NPS staff. A new way of working in approved premises is being implemented, which will lead to there always being two personnel on duty during the night rather than one. During the transition to a new way of working, NPS have agreed an additional precautionary measure which will, in some instances, provide triple cover during the two month transition period.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-12T15:39:58.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855591/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855591/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Approved Premises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many staff there were without security clearance in bail and probation hostels by site in England and Wales in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","130898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855592","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-13","<p>At the time of conviction, offenders who commit a further offence while resident at Approved Premises (AP) may have left the AP, which will therefore have no record of the conviction. To obtain the requested information, it would therefore be necessary to cross-check thousands of AP and court records, which could not be done without incurring disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-13T17:42:20.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855592/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855592/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Approved Premises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many recorded crimes were committed by people residing in bail and probation hostels by site in England and Wales in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","130899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855593","Women and Equalities","false","2018-03-15","<p>The promotion of the United Nations Sustainable Development Goal 5 and other related targets remains a priority for the Government both domestically and internationally. Government policies, such as those to support vulnerable women and girls including those that are homeless, will help us achieve the implementation of the goals.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-15T17:39:05.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855593/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855593/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-03-05","Females: Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to support the promotion of United Nations Sustainable Development Goal 5, on gender equality and the empowerment of women and girls, for women and girls who are homeless.","false","Biography information for Rosie Duffield","Canterbury","Rosie Duffield","130900"
