"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855595","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>The government is committed to tackle avoidance, evasion and non-compliance at all levels and has introduced over 100 measures since 2010 protecting over £175 billion in tax revenues. Where tax avoidance is suspected HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) investigates and challenges those arrangements, through litigation if necessary.</p><p>HMRC wins around 90% of avoidance cases taken to litigation and has protected over £6.8 billion of tax in the last three years, with many more people settling their tax affairs before reaching this stage. The marketplace for tax avoidance has shrunk in the past 4 years seeing the number of new schemes disclosed under the Disclosure of Tax Avoidance Schemes (DOTAS) regime fall by 95% since 2005/06.</p><p>Litigation outcomes and DOTAS disclosures statistics are available on GOV.UK.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-08T15:59:57.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855595/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855595/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many tax avoidance schemes HMRC has closed in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855596","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>The details that HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) collects from taxpayers on their VAT returns are not specific enough to provide the number of people benefiting from this relief. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a considerable administrative burden on businesses.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","130904","2018-03-08T12:06:53.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855596/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855596/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Empty Property: VAT Zero Rating","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received a zero rate of VAT on sales of homes that are empty for more than 10 years in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855597","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>The details that HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) collects from taxpayers on their VAT returns are not specific enough to provide the number of people benefiting from this relief. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a considerable administrative burden on businesses.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","130903","2018-03-08T12:06:53.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855597/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855597/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Museums and Galleries: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received from exemption on cultural admission charges in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855598","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>HMRC landfill tax returns do not require taxpayers to specify which relief applies to material that is not subject to tax. It is therefore not possible to establish how many taxpayers benefitted from a particular exemption. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a disproportionate administrative burden on business.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","130907","2018-03-08T16:05:35.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855598/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855598/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Landfill Tax: Dredging","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received an exemption from landfill tax for dredging waste in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855599","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-08","<p>The expert group includes members of the Building Regulations Advisory Committee (BRAC) and seconded experts. All experts on the group are invited as individuals, not representatives of an organisation, and it is not normal practice to publish their names. The names of members of BRAC are however listed at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/building-regulations-advisory-committee/about/membership" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/organisations/building-regulations-advisory-committee/about/membership</a>.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-03-08T17:10:07.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855599/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855599/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-05","Housing: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 20 February 2017 to Question 127211 on Housing: Insulation, which industry experts his Department is working with to clarify the approved documents on fire safety.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","130906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855600","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>HMRC landfill tax returns do not require taxpayers to specify which relief applies to material that is not subject to tax. It is therefore not possible to establish how many taxpayers benefitted from a particular exemption. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a disproportionate administrative burden on business.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","130905","2018-03-08T16:05:35.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855600/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855600/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Landfill Tax: Cemeteries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received an exemption from landfill tax for pet cemeteries in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855601","Treasury","false","2018-03-13","<p>HMRC does not hold sufficiently detailed information on the beneficiaries of these reliefs to be able to answer these questions. HMRC does not require this level of detail because it would place a disproportionate administrative burden on business.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","130912 ; 130914","2018-03-13T16:53:49.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855601/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855601/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Climate Change Levy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received an exemption from climate change levy for energy used in some forms of transport in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","130908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855602","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-13","<p>The government has not proposed to end entitlement to housing benefit or the housing element of universal credit to any individual in refuge. The short-term supported housing funding model will instead ensure that the housing costs for people living in refuges and other forms of short-term supported housing will be met by a grant fund administered by local authorities.</p><p>The same amount of funding as would have been available through Housing Benefit in 2020/21 will be made available as grant instead, and will directly fund bed spaces. Everyone who would be eligible under the current system to have their housing costs met by housing benefit will continue to have their housing costs met through the short-term funding model.</p><p>We are continuing to listen to the sector and are considering feedback through the current consultation which closed on 23 January, which includes sector comments on the effect of the model on the number of and services women’s refuges in England.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","130910","2018-03-13T16:04:08.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855602/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855602/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-05","Refuges: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the Government's proposals for funding short-term supported housing services from 2020 on the (a) number of and (b) services provided by women's refuges in England.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","130909"
