"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855612","Department for Education","false","2018-03-13","<p>The department operate and fund a joint team with Ofsted on unregistered schools. Ofsted can and does carry out inspections without notice where it has reasonable cause to believe that an unregistered independent school continues to operate, either at the same premises or if it has re-established elsewhere. Ofsted draws significantly on local knowledge, from the local authority and other sources, on where such settings may be operating, and has achieved great success in securing that settings close or cease operating illegally.</p><p>We work together closely with Ofsted on all of these issues, including on the extent of their powers, which we keep continually under review.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","130920","2018-03-13T15:19:09.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855612/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855612/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-05","Out-of-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that unregistered schools do not continue to operate.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","130919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855613","Department for Education","false","2018-03-13","<p>The department operate and fund a joint team with Ofsted on unregistered schools. Ofsted can and does carry out inspections without notice where it has reasonable cause to believe that an unregistered independent school continues to operate, either at the same premises or if it has re-established elsewhere. Ofsted draws significantly on local knowledge, from the local authority and other sources, on where such settings may be operating, and has achieved great success in securing that settings close or cease operating illegally.</p><p>We work together closely with Ofsted on all of these issues, including on the extent of their powers, which we keep continually under review.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","130919","2018-03-13T15:19:09.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855613/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855613/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-05","Out-of-school Education: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he has made an assessment of the potential merits of providing Ofsted with more powers to tackle unregistered schools.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","130920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855614","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-13","<p>The Government has committed to ensuring everyone across the country has easier and more convenient access to general practice services, including appointments in the evenings and weekends.</p><p> </p><p>The latest National Health Service planning guidance, issued by NHS England in February 2018, requires clinical commissioning groups to provide extended access to general practice to their whole population by 1 October 2018, to ensure additional capacity is in place ahead of winter 2018. This includes ensuring that access is available during peak times of demand, including bank holidays and across the Easter, Christmas and New Year periods. Currently, 52% of the population is benefitting from extended access, including evening and weekend appointments.</p><p> </p><p>The general practitioner (GP) Patient Survey for 2017 found that 85% of patients had a good overall experience of their GP surgery and 95% of respondents said that they have confidence and trust in their GP.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-13T13:41:09.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855614/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855614/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-05","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to improve the (a) availability and (b) adequacy of GP services as a result of the publication of the British Social Attitudes Survey.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","130921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855615","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Scottish Government will receive the equivalent spend by Network Rail in Scotland in Control Period 5, plus a population share of the equivalent change in spend in England and Wales between Control Period 5 and Control Period 6. The Scottish Government will also receive usual Barnett consequentials on any additional enhancements committed for England and Wales in due course at future fiscal events. This is consistent with current funding arrangements under the Barnett Formula.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-03-08T14:07:24.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855615/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855615/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Railways: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Secretary of State for Transport, Official Report, column 943, what the funding methodology is for the allocation of rail funding to the Scottish Government for Control Period 6.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","130922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855616","Home Office","false","2018-03-08","<p>Council tax and precept information for England is published by the Ministry for Housing, Communities and Local Government and is available at the link below.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/council-tax-levels-set-by-local-authorities-in-england-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/council-tax-levels-set-by-local-authorities-in-england-2017-to-2018</a></p><p>Information for Wales is published by the Welsh Government at:</p><p><a href="https://statswales.wales.gov.uk/Catalogue/Local-Government/Finance/Council-Tax/Budget-Requirement/budget-requirement-policeauthoritybudgetrequirement-by-policeauthority" target="_blank">https://statswales.wales.gov.uk/Catalogue/Local-Government/Finance/Council-Tax/Budget-Requirement/budget-requirement-policeauthoritybudgetrequirement-by-policeauthority</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-08T17:44:28.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855616/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855616/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-05","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total amount was that each police force received from the police precept in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","130923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855617","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-08","<p>Defra intends to publish a summary of responses to the consultation on changes to the identification of equines shortly.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-08T16:01:15.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855617/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855617/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-05","Horses: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when the Government plans to publish its summary of responses to its Consultation on changes to the identification of equines, published in Aril 2017.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","130924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855618","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Bus Services Act 2017 will enable local authorities to take steps to improve service and grow passenger numbers. This could include introducing multi operator tickets, improved vehicle standards and better connections between transport modes, employment and housing. In terms of access to hospitals via public transport, the most recent statistics show that around 94% of the population of England can reach a large hospital within an hour by public transport or walking in urban areas. In rural areas this falls to around 59% of the population.</p><p> </p><p>More generally the Government is committed to making the transport system, in urban and rural areas, accessible to all users irrespective of the reason for or destination of the journey. The draft Accessibility Action Plan, published for consultation last year, set out a number of steps we will be taking across transport modes.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-03-08T09:43:56.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855618/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855618/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-03-05","Public Transport: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the level of accessibility by public transport of hospitals in (a) Coventry and (b) the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","130925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855619","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Regional Growth Fund was established to support job creation and economic growth. The West Midlands has been allocated £430 million of RGF funding.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-08T17:56:57.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855619/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855619/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-05","Regional Growth Fund: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much Regional Growth Fund money has been allocated to the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","130926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855620","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-08","<p>According to Thinkbroadband, over 96.42% of premises in the West Midlands now have access to superfast broadband. This is up from 65% in 2010.</p><p> </p><p>There are approximately 2.5 million premises in the West Midlands region, of which 2.41 million have access to superfast broadband.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-08T11:58:55.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855620/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855620/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-05","Broadband: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many and what proportion of homes are connected to superfast broadband in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","130927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855621","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-13","<p>We expect that in June 2018 the Human Rights Council will adopt a new resolution which would renew the mandate of the Special Rapporteur. My officials in London, Geneva and in Asmara are engaged on this issue, and will be having discussions on Eritrea during the March session of the Human Rights Council.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-13T12:57:36.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855621/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855621/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-05","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he has taken to ensure that the mandate of the Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Eritrea is renewed.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","130928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855622","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-13","<p>My officials will participate in the planned Interactive Dialogue with the Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Eritrea on 12 March during the next session of the UN Human Rights Council.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-13T13:00:25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855622/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855622/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-05","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the outgoing Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Eritrea on the work conducted by her office during her time in post.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","130929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855623","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-13","<p>The United Kingdom continues to encourage the Eritrean Government to cooperate fully with the next Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Eritrea, and to invite the Rapporteur to conduct a visit. This is the best way to ensure that the Special Rapporteur has a full picture of the human rights situation in Eritrea and the mandate holder is able to support improvements in human rights in Eritrea.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-13T13:03:07.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855623/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855623/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-05","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to help ensure that the Office of the Special Rapporteur on the Situation of Human Rights in Eritrea continues to operate in a credible, neutral and effective manner.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","130930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855624","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-08","<p>According to Thinkbroadband, in Coventry South constituency over 91.44% of premises now have access to superfast broadband. This is up from 38% in 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Approximately 42,658 premises in Coventry South can now access superfast broadband out of a total of 45,500.</p><p><br> From 2020 we are also introducing a broadband Universal Service Obligation so everyone across the UK will have a clear, enforceable right to request high-speed broadband.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-08T16:34:56.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855624/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855624/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-05","Broadband: Coventry South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of homes which have been connected to superfast broadband in Coventry South constituency.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","130931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855625","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-08","<p>According to Thinkbroadband, over 95.7% of premises in Coventry now have access to superfast broadband.</p><p> </p><p>Approximately 136,461 premises in Coventry currently have access to superfast broadband.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-08T11:57:31.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855625/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855625/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-05","Broadband: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of homes which have been connected to superfast broadband in Coventry.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","130932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855626","Attorney General","false","2018-03-09","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service currently employs 183 apprentices, which equates to 3.3% of the workforce. As at 28 February 2018 the Government Legal Department had 19 apprentices representing 0.84% of the workforce. Whilst the SFO currently does not have any apprentices it does remain committed to offering apprenticeships as a means of bringing through talent and has been employing apprentices since 2011/12. There are currently no apprentices in either the Attorney General’s Office or Her Majesty’s Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-03-09T16:00:18.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855626/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855626/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-03-05","Attorney General: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many and what proportion of the staff employed by his Department are apprentices.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","130933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855627","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-12","<p>Employment and Support Allowance claimants are able to record their assessments provided they abide by reasonable conditions designed to protect the healthcare professional and the integrity of the process. They must provide a complete and accurate copy of the recording at the end of the consultation. In addition claimants can request in advance that their assessment is recorded and the assessment provider will provide the equipment.</p><p> </p><p>Personal Independence Payment claimants who wish to record their assessments can do so within existing guidelines. We are currently exploring options around the provision of recording equipment for Assessment Providers.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has set standards for the recordings to make sure that the system is fair and accurately reflects the assessment</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-12T13:11:19.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855627/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855627/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-05","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if her Department will make an assessment of the potential merits of (a) changing its guidance to allow electronic recordings of employment support allowance and personal independence payment assessments and (b) providing medical assessors with approved equipment to record those assessments; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","130934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855628","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>As set out in the Civil Service apprenticeship strategy, the Civil Service has pledged to achieve 30,000 apprenticeship starts in England by 2020, annually delivering 2.3% of our workforce in England as apprenticeship starts.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-29T09:51:24.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855628/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855628/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-05","Prime Minister: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of the staff employed in the Prime Minister's Office are apprentices.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","130935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855629","Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>There are currently 18 apprentices working at HM Treasury, which represents 1.3% of the total paid staff headcount</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-03-08T16:51:51.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855629/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855629/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-05","Treasury: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what proportion of the staff employed by his Department are apprentices.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","130936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855630","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-08","<p>This Parliamentary Question has been answered factually for Core Defra only. As at 31 January 2018 the number of Apprentices employed in the department was 32 or 1% of the total payroll workforce.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-08T13:20:03.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855630/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855630/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-05","Department For Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food, and Rural Affairs, how many and what proportion of the staff employed by his Department are apprentices.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","130937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855631","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Government is committed to the protection of vulnerable children, especially in cases where children lack adequate parental support.</p><p> </p><p>The Lord Chancellor has confirmed the start of the review into Part 1 of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012. The review will include an assessment of the changes to the scope of legal aid for immigration cases.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-03-12T15:34:14.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855631/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855631/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department plans for the review of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 to include an examination of the effect of that Act on non-asylum immigration cases involving unaccompanied and separated children.","false","Biography information for Eleanor Smith","Wolverhampton South West","Eleanor Smith","130938"
