"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855634","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-13","<p>In 2016/17 the Department for International Trade recorded a total of 56 foreign direct investments into the UK from the Republic of Ireland with the creation of 2,914 new and 751 safeguarded jobs.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-03-13T15:27:05.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855634/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855634/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-05","Foreign Investment in UK: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much foreign direct investment there was into the UK from the Republic of Ireland in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","130941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855635","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Victims’ Code is a statutory code of practice, which sets out the services that must by law be provided to victims of crime in England and Wales by criminal justice agencies. The Ministry of Justice does not collate breaches of the Code by criminal justice agencies.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-03-12T17:24:11.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855635/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855635/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many complaints have been received by his Department of alleged breaches of the Victims' Code in each of the last 3 years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855636","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-09","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given to PQ 123084 on 8<sup>th</sup> March 2018.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-09T15:12:49.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855636/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855636/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-05","Cabinet Office: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to answer Question 123084 asked on 16 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855637","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>As Minister for Victims, I meet regularly with representatives of victims groups. I chair a quarterly Victims Panel, which includes representatives of victims support organisations. This is a forum to share and learn from the experiences of victims of crime. The last meeting was in January and we will meet again in April. I also meet on a regular basis with the Victims’ Commissioner, Baroness Newlove.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-03-12T17:23:55.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855637/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855637/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he next plans to meet with representatives of victims groups.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855638","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold the requested data.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-03-12T15:34:30.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855638/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855638/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Civil Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what information his Department holds on the number of vexatious court applications taken out by people convicted of (a) stalking and (b) domestic abuse in respect of their victims in the (i) Family and (b) Civil courts.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855639","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>It is unacceptable for someone to use court processes to harass or abuse a former partner. Judges in the family and civil courts have wide powers to manage such situations, including, depending on the circumstances, the power to strike out an action they view as an abuse of process and the power to prevent a person from making further applications without prior permission of the court.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-03-12T15:35:04.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855639/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855639/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Civil Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether judges have the power to strike out an application in the family or civil court if that application is deemed to be vexatious.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855640","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-12","<p>We remain committed to addressing the issue of abusers directly cross-examining their victims in family proceedings. We want to legislate to give family courts the power to stop this as soon as possible and are considering how best to proceed.</p><p> </p><p>We would want to learn lessons from the application of such provisions in family proceedings before we consider extending them to civil proceedings.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-03-12T15:35:34.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855640/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/855640/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-03-05","Civil Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department plans to prevent convicted stalkers or domestic abusers from cross-examining their victims in family courts and civil courts.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130947"
