"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853257","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-09","<p>The UK Government has agreed to protect the rights of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU under the Withdrawal Agreement. This includes the continued recognition of EU qualifications, where recognition decisions were received or where recognition procedures were ongoing before the withdrawal date and where an EU citizen is resident in the UK on the date of withdrawal (and vice versa). The government has stated that it will seek to agree a continued system for the recognition of professional qualifications as part of the future economic partnership, and we hope to begin this phase of negotiations shortly.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-09T12:10:12.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853257/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853257/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-02","Skilled Workers: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to ensure skilled EU professionals have their professional qualifications recognised after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","130706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853258","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-08","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-08T11:51:06.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853258/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/853258/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-02","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many completed second or third personal independence payment assessment planned award reviews there have been of people with (a) Parkinson's disease, (b) multiple sclerosis, (c) motor neurone disease, (d) rheumatoid arthritis and (e) cystic fibrosis by year of repeat assessment since the introduction of personal independence payments in 2013; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","130707"
