"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852617","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-03-07T14:04:18.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852617/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852617/answer","PQ130613.pdf","PQ130613.pdf","UKSA Response","UKSA Response","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852617/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-01","Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department holds information on the number of people that died by suicide who were experiencing a financial crisis at the time of their death.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","130613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852618","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-09","<p>This Government is firmly committed to promoting and protecting the right to freedom of religion or belief around the world, and to being a strong voice internationally in defence of this fundamental right.</p><p>Freedom of religion or belief is a basic human right. The right to freedom of religion is protected by the Nigerian Constitution. We discuss human rights with the Nigerian Government and support their efforts for peaceful coexistence.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-09T16:16:07.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852618/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852618/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Nigeria: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in the Nigerian Government on respect for religious freedom.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852619","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-06","<p>We know that mental health services, including Improving Access to Psychological Therapies services, may signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care. General practitioner (GP) practices would also signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care and some practices have arrangements in place with local Citizens Advice Bureaux and debt advice services to provide outreach support in primary care.</p><p> </p><p>In January 2017, my Rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister announced the Government would review the practice of GPs charging patients experiencing debt issues to complete Mental Health Evidence Forms when they require medical evidence for their creditors. The Department is working with the Money and Mental Health Policy Institute and a range of stakeholders from the financial and debt advice sectors and the British Medical Association to undertake the review.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the impact that debt may have on mental health and wellbeing and the difficulties that may be experienced by people with mental health problems in managing their debt. The review has also considered the impact of debt and financial difficulties on people with mental health problems, including the potential impact on recovery.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-03-06T14:21:05.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852619/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852619/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-01","Mental Illness: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of debt and financial difficulty on recovery rates of people with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","130615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852620","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>The UK is strongly encouraging all sides to engage constructively with the High Level Revitalisation Forum, and we call on all parties to reconvene as soon as possible, without preconditions, to address the security and governance issues that are essential for peace. The UK Special Representative for Sudan and South Sudan was in the region to participate in both the first and second rounds of the High Level Revitalisation Forum.</p><p>The UK played a leading role in securing EU sanctions against three South Sudanese leaders in February, and we stand ready to support the efforts of the Inter-Governmental Authority on Development to ensure the consequences for those who spoil the peace process are clearly set out and effectively implemented.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-07T16:02:38.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852620/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852620/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","South Sudan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what diplomatic steps his Department is taking to help end the conflict in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852621","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-08","<p>Both the Deloitte and King’s studies have fed into the Government’s work on sleep-ins. The information requested forms part of the evidence base that is being used to assess options and is subject to further analysis and refinement. Consequently there is no timetable for publication.</p><p> </p><p>These studies have assisted Government officials in their understanding of the scale of the liabilities that the social care sector is facing.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the pressure that has been placed on the sleep-in sector by historic liabilities for back pay and is exploring options to minimise any impact on the social care sector.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","130619 ; 130644","2018-03-08T15:17:01.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852621/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852621/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-01","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, when his Department plans to publish the findings of the Deloitte and King's College audit of the liability of the social care sector for sleep-in shifts.","false","Biography information for Laura Smith","Crewe and Nantwich","Laura Smith","130617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852622","Home Office","false","2018-05-02","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the number of arrests for notifiable offences on a financial year basis. The Home Office collects and publishes these data at the offence group level, for example, ‘Sexual offences’ or ‘Miscellaneous crimes against society’. More detailed information on the specific offence or the Act under which the individual is arrested is not collected.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of arrests are published in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on convictions is the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-05-02T10:00:27.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852622/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852622/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-01","Hunting Act 2004","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) arrests and (b) convictions were made relating to offences committed under the Hunting Act 2004 in the last two years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","130618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852623","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-08","<p>Both the Deloitte and King’s studies have fed into the Government’s work on sleep-ins. The information requested forms part of the evidence base that is being used to assess options and is subject to further analysis and refinement. Consequently there is no timetable for publication.</p><p> </p><p>These studies have assisted Government officials in their understanding of the scale of the liabilities that the social care sector is facing.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the pressure that has been placed on the sleep-in sector by historic liabilities for back pay and is exploring options to minimise any impact on the social care sector.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","130617 ; 130644","2018-03-08T15:17:01.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852623/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852623/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-01","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the findings of the Deloitte and King's College audit of the liability of the social care sector for sleep-in shifts.","false","Biography information for Laura Smith","Crewe and Nantwich","Laura Smith","130619"
