"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852627","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-09","<p>Officials at the British High Commission in Dar es Salaam are following up with local authorities on the Islands of Zanzibar in relation to an alleged land dispute regarding a church and a local university in January.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-09T16:18:44.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852627/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852627/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Tanzania: Religious Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Government of Tanzania on the destruction of places of worship by local authorities within its jurisdiction; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852628","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>I have had no discussion with the Northern Ireland authorities on this issue. The FCO is responsible for supporting all British nationals overseas. Our regularly updated travel advice and our &quot;Be on the Ball&quot; campaign contains advice for all fans travelling to Russia for the World Cup.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-12T11:22:12.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852628/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852628/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Russia: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has had discussions with Northern Ireland authorities on safety advice being provided to fans travelling to the 2018 World Cup Finals; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852629","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-08","<p>Superfast broadband is now available to over 86% of homes and businesses in Northern Ireland. The current publicly-funded superfast broadband roll-out project in Northern Ireland is due to complete this month and will have provided coverage to 41,000 premises. The UK government funding for this project was £7.054 million. Given the scale of the challenge in delivering broadband coverage in Northern Ireland, the UK government allocated a further £150 million for ultrafast broadband in Northern Ireland in the June 2017 funding agreement for Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>The government has regular discussions with the Northern Ireland authorities on both the delivery of the current project and proposals for taking forward new funding.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-08T12:58:12.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852629/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852629/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-01","Broadband: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with the Northern Ireland authorities on the roll-out of superfast and ultrafast broadband in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852630","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-07","<p>Defence cooperation between the UK and Israel is strong and supports the UK's role in coalition success against Daesh and promotes regional stability.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-07T15:55:57.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852630/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852630/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-01","Israel: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of security co operation between the UK and Israel.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852631","Department for Education","false","2018-03-09","<p>The Higher Education Statistics Agency collects and publishes statistics on staff employed at UK Higher Education Institutions (HEIs). Annual statistics on staff employed by HEIs are published under the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.hesa.ac.uk/data-and-analysis/statistical-first-releases" target="_blank">https://www.hesa.ac.uk/data-and-analysis/statistical-first-releases</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In the academic year 2016/17, 12% of staff with known nationality were EU nationals and 8% were non-EU nationals at UK HEIs.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-03-09T11:35:44.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852631/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852631/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-01","Universities: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of  staff employed by UK Universities are citizens of (a) another EU member state (b) a non-EU state.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852632","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-09","<p>The UK and Jamaica have a strong relationship. Our Governments cooperate effectively on prosperity, development, justice and law enforcement for the benefit of all our citizens. Our membership of the Commonwealth underpins our shared values. 800,000 people in the UK have Jamaican family connections and over 200,000 Britons visit Jamaica each year. The Government of the UK and its Caribbean trading partners have agreed that future trade arrangements after the UK leaves the EU, will take existing arrangements as the starting point. The UK-Caribbean Infrastructure Fund has allocated £53 million to support development in Jamaica.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-09T15:56:03.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852632/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852632/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Jamaica: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the strength of the UK's relationship with Jamaica when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","130628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852633","Department for Education","false","2018-03-09","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-03-09T09:59:29.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852633/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852633/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-01","Universities: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of academic staff employed by UK universities spend more than 180 days working in academic institutions in other EU member states as part of their contract of employment.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","130629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852634","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-07","<p>The Government are committed to getting the best possible deal for the United Kingdom - a deal that works for all parts of the UK, including the North East.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>By leaving the Customs Union and establishing a new and ambitious customs arrangement with the EU, we will be able to forge new trade relationships with our partners around the world, which we believe will boost the economies of regions like the North East.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We are undertaking a wide range of analysis and preparatory work that will contribute to our exit negotiations with the EU, to define our future partnership with the EU, and to inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK’s domestic policies and frameworks.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>However, ministers have a specific responsibility, which Parliament has endorsed, not to release information that could expose our negotiating position.</p><p><strong></strong><br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-03-07T10:13:49.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852634/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852634/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-01","UK Trade with EU: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment he has made of the economic consequences for the North East of leaving the Customs Union after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","130630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852635","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-08","<p>We are aware that Italian oil company ENI has been prevented from carrying out licensed drilling in Cyprus’ Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) following Navtex issued by Turkey warning of naval exercises in the same area. We support the Republic of Cyprus’ sovereign right to exploit natural resources in its EEZ, and want to see exploration go ahead. We believe Cyprus’ hydrocarbons should be developed for the benefit of all Cypriots, and urge all parties to look for ways by which the development of hydrocarbons can support the search for a settlement.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-08T08:44:23.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852635/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852635/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852635/answer/previousversion/45422","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Cyprus: Territorial Waters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the naval security situation in the territorial waters of the Republic of Cyprus.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","130631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852636","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office has raised recent developments in Cyprus's maritime Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) with Turkey. We support the Republic of Cyprus' sovereign right to exploit natural resources in its EEZ, and want to see exploration go ahead. We believe Cyprus' hydrocarbons should be developed for the benefit of all Cypriots, and urge all parties to look for ways by which the development of hydrocarbons can support the search for a settlement.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-08T08:48:12.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852636/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852636/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852636/answer/previousversion/45424","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Cyprus: Territorial Waters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in Turkey regarding Turkish Navy ships operating in proximity to the territorial waters of the Republic of Cyprus.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","130632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852637","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-06","<p>​We are aware of the Republic of Cyprus's recent reports to the UN about Turkish violations of its airspace over the northern part of the island. In line with UN Security Council Resolution 550, the UK does not recognise the self-declared &quot;Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus&quot; as an independent state. The UK recognises only one Cypriot state – the Republic of Cyprus – and only one government as the sole legitimate government. We are aware of the Republic of Cyprus's recent reports to the UN about Turkish violations of its airspace over the northern part of the island. In line with UN Security Council Resolution 550, the UK does not recognise the self-declared &quot;Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus&quot; as an independent state. The UK recognises only one Cypriot state – the Republic of Cyprus – and only one government as the sole legitimate government.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-06T17:37:41.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852637/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852637/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-01","Cyprus: Air Space","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether his Department has recently received reports of Cypriot airspace being entered by Turkish aircraft.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","130633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852638","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-06","<p>Details of ministerial meetings are published in the Department's Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on GOV.UK.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-03-06T17:07:48.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852638/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852638/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-01","Shanker Singham ","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, the hon. Member for Wycombe has held meetings with Shanker Singham in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","130634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852639","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-06","<p>We know that mental health services, including Improving Access to Psychological Therapies services, may signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care. General Practitioner (GP) practices would also signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care and some practices have arrangements in place with local Citizens Advice Bureaux and debt advice services to provide outreach support in primary care.</p><p> </p><p>In January 2017, my Rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister announced the Government would review the practice of GPs charging patients experiencing debt issues to complete Mental Health Evidence Forms when they require medical evidence for their creditors. The Department is working with the Money and Mental Health Policy Institute and a range of stakeholders from the financial and debt advice sectors and the British Medical Association to undertake the review.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the impact that debt may have on mental health and wellbeing and the difficulties that may be experienced by people with mental health problems in managing their debt. The review has also considered the impact of debt and financial difficulties on people with mental health problems, including the potential impact on recovery.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","130638","2018-03-06T14:30:30.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852639/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852639/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-01","Mental Illness: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of support available to people experiencing mental health difficulties to help them manage their personal finances.","true","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","130635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852640","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-08","<p>The government is committed to building an economy that works for everyone, including those experiencing mental health difficulties.</p><p> </p><p>The Regulation of consumer credit is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). The government has given the FCA strong powers to protect consumers. It requires all lenders to treat customers fairly, and to establish appropriate policies for dealing with vulnerable customers, including those with mental health difficulties.</p><p> </p><p>We have passed the honourable lady’s question on to the FCA, who will reply directly to her by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-03-08T12:21:46.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852640/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852640/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-03-01","Financial Services: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that financial lenders provide appropriate support to customers experiencing mental health difficulties.","true","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","130636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852641","Department for Education","false","2018-03-06","<p>The attached table shows apprenticeship starts by gender and sector subject area for each local authority district in the 2016/17 academic year.</p><p> </p><p>For additional information on apprenticeships by geographic and demographic breakdowns, please see the apprenticeships geography data tool and the apprenticeships demographic data tool in the ‘FE data library’:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-03-06T17:41:48.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852641/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852641/answer","130637 attachment.xlsx","130637 attachment.xlsx","Apprenticeships by Sector, Subject Area & Gender","Apprenticeships by Sector, Subject Area & Gender","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852641/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-01","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) women and (b) men in each local authority area in England started an apprenticeship in each sector subject area in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852642","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-06","<p>We know that mental health services, including Improving Access to Psychological Therapies services, may signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care. General Practitioner (GP) practices would also signpost patients to debt advice services as part of their care and some practices have arrangements in place with local Citizens Advice Bureaux and debt advice services to provide outreach support in primary care.</p><p> </p><p>In January 2017, my Rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister announced the Government would review the practice of GPs charging patients experiencing debt issues to complete Mental Health Evidence Forms when they require medical evidence for their creditors. The Department is working with the Money and Mental Health Policy Institute and a range of stakeholders from the financial and debt advice sectors and the British Medical Association to undertake the review.</p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the impact that debt may have on mental health and wellbeing and the difficulties that may be experienced by people with mental health problems in managing their debt. The review has also considered the impact of debt and financial difficulties on people with mental health problems, including the potential impact on recovery.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","130635","2018-03-06T14:30:30.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852642/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852642/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-01","Mental Illness: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of debt and financial difficulty on recovery rates of people mental health problems.","true","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","130638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852643","Department for Education","false","2018-03-08","<p>There are no academy schools that have had their funding agreement terminated without a new trust identified to take over from the point at which termination comes into effect. The department would not leave a gap between funding agreements in any re-brokerage case, as the school would not be in receipt of any funding and therefore could not operate.</p><p> </p><p>The Deed of Novation and/or Variation is the preferred route when academies are being re-brokered; as the Deed of Novation and/or Variation gives greater continuity for the academy.</p><p> </p><p>The costs publication that lists the cases that have been re-brokered can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academy-trust-transfers-and-grant-funding" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academy-trust-transfers-and-grant-funding</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","130641","2018-03-08T16:08:09.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852643/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852643/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-01","Academies: Sponsorship","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 20 February 2018 to Question 127246, on Schools: Standards, if he will list the (a) number and (b) names of academy schools which have had their funding agreement terminated and have not yet been re-brokered.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","130639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852644","Department for Education","false","2018-03-06","<p>Educational achievement, irrespective of background, is at the heart of our commitment to make this a country where everyone has a fair chance to go as far as their talent and hard work will take them. The department recognises that children from poor backgrounds may face additional challenges to realising their potential. It has spent over £11 billion since 2011, almost £2.5 billion this year alone, through the pupil premium to provide schools with resources to overcome the barriers to learning so often experienced by disadvantaged pupils. Over 9,700 pupils in East Ham are eligible for support and this year their schools are receiving more than £11 million through the pupil premium.</p><p>We look to schools to use this extra funding effectively. We know from research that a personalised approach, drawing on well-evidenced strategies, generally produces good results. Studies by the National Foundation for Educational Research and the regularly-updated toolkit maintained by the Education Endowment Foundation provide support to school leaders in their decision-making. Schools all over England are overcoming the poor economic circumstances of their disadvantaged pupils; examples of effective practice are highlighted each year through our national Pupil Premium Awards.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-06T16:12:04.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852644/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/852644/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-01","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taking to ensure that child poverty does not have a detrimental effect on educational attainment.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130640"
